<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Challenges</title>
  <link href="/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <link href="/css/customize.css" rel="stylesheet"/>
  <script src="/js/jquery.min.js"></script>
  <script src="/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">

  <div class="text-center" id="welcome-message">
    <h1>Welcome to Web Security Challenge Website!</h1>
    <p>
      In this website, there are 4 security flaws, try to find them, have fun!
    </p>
    <p id="remind-submit-token">
      <span class="alert alert-warning">
        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-warning-sign"></span> <strong>Heads up!</strong> Once you complete any challenge, a secret token will be assign to you,
        please follow instruction to <a class="text-primary" href="http://<%= request.host %>:9000/score" target="_blank">submit it</a>.
      </span>
    </p>
  </div>

  <hr/>

  <div class="challenge-description">
    <h4>Challenge 1, SQL Injection</h4>
    <p>
      The password field is SQL Injection vulnerable, try login the system (username: <strong>Jerry</strong>) by SQL Injection, without using correct password.<br />
    </p>
    <p><a href="/customer/login" target="_blank" class="btn btn-info btn-sm"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-play"></span> Click here to start</a></p>
  </div>

  <div class="challenge-description">
    <h4>Challenge 2, Hidden Admin Management URL & Careless Developer</h4>
    <div>
      <p>
        <strong>Part 1:</strong> Admin manage URL was hidden, try to find clue and access that URL.<br />
        <strong>Hint:</strong> You know there are some 'common' files in website...
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Part 2:</strong> When you find the hidden manage URL, try to login as admin user.<br />
        <strong>Hint:</strong> No security flaws in the login process, but developers are notorious for leaving statements
        like FIXME's, TODO's, Code Broken, Hack, etc... inside the source code.
      </p>
      <p><a href="/customer/login" target="_blank" class="btn btn-info btn-sm"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-play"></span> Click here to start</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="challenge-description">
    <h4>Challenge 3, Cross-Site Scripting</h4>
    <p>
      Cross-Site Scripting vulnerability exist in product search page,
      try to popup a javascript alert window by this vulnerability.
    </p>
    <p><a href="/product/search" target="_blank" class="btn btn-info btn-sm"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-play"></span> Click here to start</a></p>
  </div>

  <div class="challenge-description">
    <h4>Challenge 4, Missing Function Level Access Control</h4>
    <p>
      Users in this website are not allowed to view other user's profile, but the access control is missing or insufficient.<br />
      Login as user <strong>Tom</strong> (username: tom / password: cat), and try to view other user's profile.
    </p>
    <p><a href="/customer/login" target="_blank" class="btn btn-info btn-sm"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-play"></span> Click here to start</a></p>
  </div>

</div>

</body>
</html>
